# nclawzero-ssh-keys / authorized_keys.example
#
# THIS FILE IS COMMITTED.  It documents the format expected by the
# nclawzero-ssh-keys recipe.  The actual fleet-internal key list lives
# in a sibling file `authorized_keys` (no .example suffix), which is
# gitignored — never published to gitlab.com / github.com.
#
# To populate the real file before building:
#
#   1. Copy this file:
#      cp recipes-core/nclawzero-ssh-keys/files/authorized_keys.example \
#         recipes-core/nclawzero-ssh-keys/files/authorized_keys
#
#   2. Replace the placeholder lines below with your fleet's real
#      ssh-ed25519 / ssh-rsa pubkey lines.
#
#   3. Sanity-check: `git status` must NOT show
#      recipes-core/nclawzero-ssh-keys/files/authorized_keys as
#      tracked — the .gitignore rule keeps it local-only.
#
# Format (one key per line, comment field is informational):
#   ssh-<type> <base64> <comment-descriptive-of-workstation>
#
# Idempotency: every nclawzero-ssh-keys build replaces /home/<user>/.ssh/
# authorized_keys wholesale; nothing accumulates across re-builds.
# Rotation = edit this file + rebuild image.
#
# Both recipients (ncz operator + jasonperlow backup user) get the SAME
# authorized_keys content; the second user is a defense-in-depth
# foothold for when the operator account is disrupted (cf. 2026-04-26
# Trixie userconfig stripping clawpi+zeropi accounts at first boot).

# Replace these placeholder lines with real fleet workstation keys:
ssh-ed25519 AAAAREPLACEME jperlow@<workstation-name>
# ssh-ed25519 AAAAREPLACEME <user>@<host>
